IHA appoints Eddie Rich as new CEO Celebrating our 25th anniversary The International Hydropower Association (IHA) was founded a quarter of a century ago in 1995. 
our story Facts about Hydropower Get the full picture History of Hydropower From its birth to the modern era Hydropower worldwide Explore regions and countries Types of Hydropower Learn about the technology Who we are Our mission Get the full picture with our quick facts about hydropower About IHA Get the full picture with our quick facts about hydropower Our members Get the full picture with our quick facts about hydropower Our team Get the full picture with our quick facts about hydropower Our board Get the full picture with our quick facts about hydropower Our story Get the full picture with our quick facts about hydropower What we do Our priorities Energy Climate Sustainability Finance Modernisation Water How we work Good practice Policy Research Networking Training Recognition Annual report Our 2020-2021 report Knowledge networks Join our communities Covid-19 News and resources News and events News Press releases and announcements Events The World Hydropower Congress and other upcoming events Blog Insights from experts and decision-makers The World Hydropower Congress Insights from experts and decision-makers Videos Insights from experts and decision-makers Resources Publications Download our public reports Tools Find sustainability tools Status Report Sector insights and statistics Facts About Hydropower Get the full picture Innovations Hub Explore case studies hydropower pro Join our online community join us International Association of the Year hydropower pro Celebrating our 25th anniversary The International Hydropower Association (IHA) was founded a quarter of a century ago in 1995. 
our story Facts about Hydropower Get the full picture History of Hydropower From its birth to the modern era Hydropower worldwide Explore regions and countries Types of Hydropower Learn about the technology Who we are Our mission Our mission is to advance sustainable hydropower About IHA We are a non-profit membership organisation Our members View our directory of organisations operating in over 120 countries Our team IHA's Central Office manages our work programmes Our board IHA's Board governs the association on behalf of members Our story The voice of sustainable hydropower for a quarter of a century What we do Our priorities Energy Climate Sustainability Finance Modernisation Water How we work Good practice Policy Research Networking Training Recognition Annual report Our 2020-2021 report Knowledge networks Join our communities Covid-19 News and resources News and events News Press releases and announcements Events The World Hydropower Congress and other upcoming events Blog Insights from experts and decision-makers The World Hydropower Congress Find out more about the 2021 World Hydropower Congress Videos Watch our latest videos and webinars Resources Publications Download our public reports Tools Find sustainability tools Status Report Sector insights and statistics Facts About Hydropower Get the full picture Innovations Hub Explore case studies hydropower pro Join our online community join us International Association of the Year hydropower pro 17 July 2019 The International Hydropower Association (IHA) has appointed Eddie Rich as its new Chief Executive Officer, following a global recruitment search led by the association’s board, it was announced today.     
Mr Rich will take up his appointment on 9 September 2019. 
He succeeds Richard M Taylor who is stepping down to work as an independent consultant and who will support the new CEO in a consultative capacity through 2020. 
In a statement, IHA President Ken Adams said: “Mr Rich will bring to the role extensive international experience, most recently as a founder and senior executive of the EITI. IHA welcomes Mr Rich and looks forward to working with him as the hydropower sector helps to contribute solutions to the energy transition challenges faced by the world today.” 
Mr Rich said: “There is need for a bigger and better contribution to green energy from hydropower. IHA is the key organisation to make sure that the industry is well informed about good practices, has the capacity to implement them, and the world benefits from the best use of this precious technology. IHA's work on building and sharing high quality and evidence-based knowledge is critically important.” “Much has been done. There is much to do. I look forward to taking this forward with an excellent team. I pay tribute to Richard Taylor who has brought us so far with unparalleled passion, knowledge and skill. I look forward to working with him to ensure a strong and smooth transition.”     Eddie Rich's biography IHA’s incoming CEO, Eddie Rich, has worked on the role of corporates in international development for over 20 years. 
He has been Deputy Head of the EITI since the international secretariat was established in 2007, including a period as its Executive Director. 
His responsibilities have included leading on EITI implementation globally and overseeing the organisation’s finance, human resources and communications functions, as well as the organisation of its triennial global conference. 
He has also published books and articles on governance entrepreneurship and multi-stakeholder governance. 
His prior experience includes working as the UK Government Department for International Development (DFID)’s representative to Angola and deputy head in Kenya, and as head of DFID's corporate social responsibility team. 
He has degrees from the University of Oxford and the University of Westminster. 
